SNC-263 This changeset includes updates for useBackground as well.
Implemented a NotificationCenter post whenever preferences are updated and the updated the lcoation manager to listen for those updates as useLocation should enable the lcoation manager immediately.
However useBackground is different in that an app should only try and enter the background when it's being put there by the system, so it simply looks at the preference when that event occurs

SNC-272 Cleanup SonicLocationHandler, remove constant registering for regions
The logic has been dramatically cleaned up and now creates an add/remove list as an NSArray and only adjusts the monitored regions as needed.
The debugging functionality was also cleaned up to use built in appending of files.
All methods were documented

SNC-273 In SonicLocationHandler use the correct foot to meter conversion, maybe in SonicLocation
Fixed parseData in SonicLocation so that it automatically converts feet to meters and then moved methods that were hacked into SonicAPI over to SonicUtility where they should live

SNC-262 Switch FMDatabase to new version and use the FMDatabaseQueue functionality to ensure thread consistency
Replaced the previous FMDB lib with the new FMDB lib and attempted to replace all FMDatabase access calls with direct FMDatabaseQueue calls.
- All were replaced - HOWEVER: while testing I realized that there where several deadlocks as we were trying to lock the db at several levels. It APPEARS that there are no current issues with this.
SNC-275 has been created as the task where the entire persistence system should be revisited

SNC-262 Switch FMDatabase to new version and use the FMDatabaseQueue functionality to ensure thread consistency
A few more changes were required as additional deadlocks were found

SNC-259 Implement microsite support in widgets
Added Objective-Zip library to UI SDK
Added callback to SonicCacheDownloaderDelegate for processing files after receipt
Implementation is a bit hackie, and the whole cache system should be revised, but as more of a content provider platform, but it does work.

SNC-197 Content Viewer functionality
Refactored viewer to more simply support extension
Now it just needs a selector dispatch map for actions and it will be pretty descent
Supported callbacks on both ipad and iphone -actionsheet -takePicture -getuuid -tweet -tweetPic -email -flash -dismissKeyboard -set/get/remove values

Added the math that Alex neglected to do in order to determine timing and then determined that the encoded file provided by Alex had incorrect encoding
~1s -> ~2s > ~1s
should be
~1s > ~1s > ~1s
Once alex fixes his file encoding this should be working.
